## Product Domain (TCG sealed + graded — post May 2026 pivot)

HOKO is strictly sealed product + PSA/BGS/CGC slabs going forward. No new singles sourcing.

**In scope:**

- Pokémon TCG sealed (boxes, ETBs, booster packs, decks, promos)
- Magic: The Gathering sealed
- One Piece TCG sealed
- Dragon Ball Super sealed
- Japanese sealed (Pokémon, One Piece, DBS, etc.)
- Graded slabs — PSA / BGS / CGC only
- Collection buyback service (sealed + verified-grader slabs only)

**Out of scope (sell-through existing, don't replenish):**

- Loose singles — existing Shopify/eBay stock clears naturally
- Mystery packs / bulk single lots
- Slabs from unverified graders (HGA, GMG, etc.)

## Channel Strategy (post sealed-only pivot)

| Channel | Role | What goes here |
|---------|------|----------------|
| **Shopify** | Brand experience + margin | Sealed product + PSA/BGS/CGC slabs. Existing premium singles sell-through, no new singles. |
| **eBay** | Search-driven acquisition | Sealed + slabs. Captures buyers who search the platform directly. Insert bridge stays. |
| **Whatnot** | On-demand live | Sealed pack-rip / box-break shows when owner chooses to go live. |

**Bridge plan:** every eBay parcel includes a printed insert with HOKO10 + Shopify URL to convert eBay buyers into Shopify customers.

**Pivot in progress:** existing Shopify products under AUD $30 (overwhelmingly cheap singles) are being archived in one pass (reversible). Owner can do this via:
- The script `scripts/shopify/archive_cheap_singles.py` in the cloud repo, OR
- The Shopify Connector for Claude — voice prompt: *"Show me Shopify products priced under $30 AUD, don't archive yet."* Then *"Go ahead and archive those."*

Premium singles (≥$30) stay listed and sell through naturally.

## Sourcing

All new sourcing is **sealed + verified-grader slabs only.** No more lot-splitting, no more single-card sourcing.

- **Japanese / Korean / Chinese sealed:** mix of direct-from-Asia and AU-based wholesale partners — varies per SKU. **Default copy is generic:** *"sourced through our regional supplier network"* or *"imported via our wholesale partners."* Only say *"direct from Japan"* (or similar) when owner has confirmed for that SKU. Ask before writing if unsure.
- **English sealed:** AU-based wholesalers + opportunistic sealed lots from buybacks.
- **Graded slabs:** primarily from collection buybacks. Always verify grader (PSA / BGS / CGC only).
- Margin profile is now consistent (supplier-bought, predictable). Apply replacement-cost pricing on every SKU (see Brand & Pricing Strategy §1).

